{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611604","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611604"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:12:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:12:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16228"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16228","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16228"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.38,0.23,0.19,0.08,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8919"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72923"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8919","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8919"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16228"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58393"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"262"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7017"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"10146"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21229"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21234"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72923","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72923"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EFibrocystic change is a common benign condition of the breast that typically affects women of reproductive age.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the pathophysiology of fibrocystic change?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Primarily affects terminal duct lobular units","Results from increased progesterone levels","Develops due to decreased estrogen sensitivity","Occurs mainly in post-menopausal women","Causes atrophy of breast stroma"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrocystic change primarily affects the terminal duct lobular units (TDLUs)\u003C/strong\u003E of the breast. The condition is characterised by cyst formation, stromal fibrosis, and epithelial proliferation in response to hormonal stimulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe condition does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eresult from increased progesterone levels,\u003C/strong\u003E but with relative oestrogen predominance. It does not \u003Cstrong\u003Edevelop due to decreased oestrogen sensitivity\u003C/strong\u003E, as the tissue remains hormone-responsive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFibrocystic change typically does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eoccur mainly in post-menopausal women, \u003C/strong\u003E(unless they are on hormone replacement therapy). It affects women during their reproductive years. The condition does not \u003Cstrong\u003Ecause atrophy of breast stroma\u003C/strong\u003E but instead leads to stromal fibrosis and increased density.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe condition is influenced by hormonal fluctuations during the menstrual cycle and tends to be most symptomatic during the luteal phase.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fibrocystic change primarily affects the terminal duct lobular units (TDLUs) in the upper outer quadrant of the breast","Fibrocystic change is associated with an increased oestrogen to progesterone ratio.","Fibrocystic change is characterised by cyst formation, stromal fibrosis, and epithelial proliferation."],"references":["Dang BQ, Miles B, Young P, He J, Nguyen QD. An Interesting Imaging Presentation of a Common Benign Entity: Fibrocystic Changes in a Postmenopausal Patient. Cureus. 2023 Mar 17;15(3):e36292. doi: 10.7759/cureus.36292. PMID: 37073209; PMCID: PMC10106097.","Malherbe K, Khan M, Fatima S. Fibrocystic Breast Disease. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31869073.","Bennett DL, Buckley A, Lee MV. Fibrocystic Change. Radiol Clin North Am. 2024 Jul;62(4):581-592. doi: 10.1016/j.rcl.2023.12.008. Epub 2024 Mar 7. PMID: 38777535.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58393"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16228"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58393","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58393"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T18:15:40+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T15:32:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8919"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72923"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Le